\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {4}{\ignorespaces Ellipsoidal verification benchmark rendered in 3D. The ellipsoid is clipped along a symmetry plane to expose the interior solution field. Panel\nobreakspace  {}(a) shows the predicted field $u_h$, which peaks at the center and vanishes on the boundary as expected for the quadratic exact solution $u^*=1-(\xi ^2+\eta ^2+\zeta ^2)$. Panel\nobreakspace  {}(b) shows the absolute error $|u_h-u^*|$, confirming that the operator pullback and the analytic geometric map are implemented correctly (relative $L^2$ error $=2.26\times 10^{-3}$, maximum error $=5.23\times 10^{-3}$).\relax }}{12}{figure.caption.5}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:forward_poisson_ellipsoid}{{4}{12}{Ellipsoidal verification benchmark rendered in 3D. The ellipsoid is clipped along a symmetry plane to expose the interior solution field. Panel~(a) shows the predicted field $u_h$, which peaks at the center and vanishes on the boundary as expected for the quadratic exact solution $u^*=1-(\xi ^2+\eta ^2+\zeta ^2)$. Panel~(b) shows the absolute error $|u_h-u^*|$, confirming that the operator pullback and the analytic geometric map are implemented correctly (relative $L^2$ error $=2.26\times 10^{-3}$, maximum error $=5.23\times 10^{-3}$).\relax }{figure.caption.5}{}}
