\newlabel{fig:torus_inverse_original_convergence}{{10}{18}{Parameter convergence history for the global torus optimizer. (a)~Relative errors of~$\mu $ and~$K$ decrease monotonically over 100 epochs, reaching ${\sim }10^{-2}\%$ for both parameters. (b)~Traction mismatch~$\mathcal {L}_{\mathrm {trac}}$ decreases by five orders of magnitude from initialization to the $10^{-8}$ level. The oscillatory pattern in~(a) reflects the alternating descent directions in the two-parameter landscape.\relax }{figure.caption.14}{}}
\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {11}{\ignorespaces Schwarz-based distributed parameter identification on the torus, rendered from VTU exports. Top row: traction-mode Schwarz. Bottom row: displacement-mode Schwarz. (a,\tmspace  +\thinmuskip {.1667em}c)\nobreakspace  {}Observation-error magnitude on the torus surface; the traction-mode error is roughly $10\times $ larger than the displacement-mode error. (b,\tmspace  +\thinmuskip {.1667em}d)\nobreakspace  {}Per-chart shear-modulus estimate\nobreakspace  {}$\mathaccentV {hat}05E{\mu }_i$ mapped onto the torus surface; the color range is $[1.79,\tmspace  +\thinmuskip {.1667em}1.81]$ centered on $\mu _{\mathrm  {true}}=1.8$. In displacement mode\nobreakspace  {}(d), the surface is nearly uniform, consistent with the machine-precision inter-chart consensus ($\mu $ std $= 1.47\times 10^{-13}$) reported in Table\nobreakspace  {}\ref  {tab:torus_comparison}.\relax }}{19}{figure.caption.15}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:torus_schwarz_3d}{{11}{19}{Schwarz-based distributed parameter identification on the torus, rendered from VTU exports. Top row: traction-mode Schwarz. Bottom row: displacement-mode Schwarz. (a,\,c)~Observation-error magnitude on the torus surface; the traction-mode error is roughly $10\times $ larger than the displacement-mode error. (b,\,d)~Per-chart shear-modulus estimate~$\hat {\mu }_i$ mapped onto the torus surface; the color range is $[1.79,\,1.81]$ centered on $\mu _{\mathrm {true}}=1.8$. In displacement mode~(d), the surface is nearly uniform, consistent with the machine-precision inter-chart consensus ($\mu $ std $= 1.47\times 10^{-13}$) reported in Table~\ref {tab:torus_comparison}.\relax }{figure.caption.15}{}}
